            "activeRemotePortCount":"0",
            "comments":"This is a stress test which simply generates a very high volume of objects with no content for the sole purpose of isolating the speed at which general framework operations can occur.\n\nLargely it establishes how quickly the framework can checkpoint/commit operations against the write ahead log.  This flow would also expose performance degradation brought about by inappropriately low heap sizes, provenance performance, logging configurations, etc..",
